25/04/2010
BELGRADE, Serbia -- Tomislav Nikolic was re-elected on Saturday (April 24th) as the leader of the opposition Serbian Progressive Party (SNS) at the party's congress in Belgrade. More than 3,000 delegates attended. Nikolic says the SNS supports Serbia's EU integration and will work to fight corruption and crime. He also reiterated that Kosovo is part of Serbia but voiced his party's willingness to hold talks with Albanian representatives. (Tanjug, RTS, B92 - 24/04/10)
